(36, 1, '2015-02-21 23:28:54', '2015-02-21 23:28:54', '<div class="article-header">\r\n\r\n<hr class="hidden-xs" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-8">\r\n<div class="article-photo"><img class="img-responsive" src="http://images5.aplus.com/uc-up/980c310f-de18-45f1-972e-501991eaeafb/980c310f-de18-45f1-972e-501991eaeafb.crop_728x384_0,7.resize_1200x630.scale_crop_1200x630.stretch_on.format_jpeg.inline_yes" alt="These Twins Can See Through Each Other''s Eyes, But That''s Not The Only Thing That''s Amazing About Them" /></div>\r\n<div class="article-byline-comments">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-xs-7"><span class="author">by <a class="name" href="http://aplus.com/u/KSAPlus" rel="author">K.S. ANTHONY</a></span></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-5">\r\n<div class="comments-count"><i class="fa fa-comment"></i> <span class="count"><span class="fb_comments_count">0</span> </span><span class="hidden-xs">comments</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<div class="article-connecting-blocks">\r\n<div class="connecting-blocks">\r\n<div class="btn-group btn-group-justified"><a class="btn btn-lg btn-default facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Faplus.com%2Fa%2Fhogan-twins-beauty" target="_blank" data-track-share="facebook"><i class="fa fa-facebook-square"></i> Share</a><a class="btn btn-lg btn-default twitter" href="https://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Faplus.com%2Fa%2Fhogan-twins-beauty&amp;text=These%20Twins%20Can%20See%20Through%20Each%20Other%27s%20Eyes%2C%20But%20That%27s%20Not%20The%20Only%20Thing%20That%27s%20Amazing%20About%20Them%20via%20%40aplusapp" target="_blank" data-track-share="twitter"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i> Tweet</a><a class="btn btn-lg subscribe btn-default" data-toggle="#subscribe_area">Subscribe</a>\r\n<div class="visible-md-inline visible-lg-inline">to A+</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="article-content">\r\n<h2>These girls can see through each other''s eyes.</h2>\r\n<div class="block-image-wrapper" data-width="350"><img src="http://images5.aplus.com/uc-up/762b8b0b-d90f-410c-8871-8d565111594a/762b8b0b-d90f-410c-8871-8d565111594a.quality_lighter.inline_yes.png" alt="This video features Tatiana and Krista Ho" /><a class="image-source" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BwM1qBN8SP0" target="_blank">www.youtube.com</a></div>\r\nThis video features<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krista_and_Tatiana_Hogan" target="_blank"> Tatiana and Krista Hogan</a>, 8-year-old craniopagus conjoined twins from Vancouver, British Columbia.\r\n\r\nTatiana and Krista are very special. Not only are the girls joined at the back and side of their heads, they also <a href="http://multiples.about.com/od/conjoinedprofiles/p/cthogan.htm" target="_blank">share a part of the brain</a>: the <a href="http://www.news-medical.net/health/What-does-the-Thalamus-do.aspx" target="_blank">thalamus</a>, which controls most sensory processing, including sight, hearing, and touch, but also manages movement and coordination.\r\n\r\nThe Daily Mail reported one of the most extraordinary things about them: <a href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1331769/Doctors-stunned-conjoined-twins-share-brain-thoughts.html" target="_blank">They can see through each other''s eyes</a> and "hear" each other''s thoughts.\r\n\r\nBut there''s more to these young women than just their miraculous biology. They can inspire us to reconsider how we approach beauty.\r\n<h2>This video challenges us to rethink not just the way we think of others, but the way we think of ourselves.</h2>\r\n<div class="partial-width-embed-80">\r\n<div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9 " data-aspect-ratio="100.0"><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/BwM1qBN8SP0?rel=0&amp;start=0&amp;end=70&amp;autoplay=0" width="100%" height="100%" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>"Imagine if we could help all young women know how